bark up
Homonym Number:
Word Class: verb
Sense Number:
Definition:[mustering] to signal a musterer's presence by instructing dogs to bark or to command one's dogs to bark to make a mob move at a particular stage in a muster.


Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain: Rural
Region: [none]
